article.headline: LIU 70, New Hampshire 62
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Williams sank two free throws with 12 seconds remaining in regulation to tie it up, then added eight points in overtime to finish with 21 and lead LIU to a 70-62 victory over New Hampshire on Saturday. Eugene Kotorobai came off the bench to score 12 points and grab 10 rebounds for the Blackbirds (3-4), who trailed 29-28 at halftime. Blagoj Janev topped the Wildcats (1-6) with 18 points. Jermaine Anderson and Mike Christensen had 13 apiece. After tying it 61-61, Williams opened the overtime with a jumper to ignite the 9-1 surge.
